This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 10:24 a.m.  Def appears from ICJ, in custody.  Atty Douglas Muskett appears with def.  Matthew J. Tingstad appears for the State of WI.  Case set for continued initial.  Complaint has been received by def.  Def is contesting extradition at this time.  Atty Muskett explains MN charges.  Indicates def has counsel in MN.  Court questions DA.  DA indicates MN ready to come get def.  Def requesting a cash bond.  Atty Muskett states reasons for bond request.  Court in recess briefly.  DA requests $5,000 cash bond.  States reasons for request.  Atty Muskett argues def has local ties.  Charges are on ly misd. in MN.  Requests $500 to $1,000.  Court sets $5,000 cash bond.  Counsel can file a motion to reconsider.  10:37 a.m  Court in recess again briefly.  10:40 a.m.  BOR:  Def wants extradition held.  Def is going to post cash bond.  Court is not setting extradition hearing now.  Def no to be in ICJ to exceed 30 days if cannot post.  Court advises def of bond conditions.  Must appear at all future court dates.  Def provides updated address.  Adj.  10:43 a.m.  klr
Adjourned initial appearance on January 18, 2022 at 10:30 am.

11:39 a.m.  Court calls case.  Def present, in custody.  Matthew J. Tingstad appears for the State of WI.  Court explains right to counsel.  Def indicates wants atty and has atty for this case.  Court indicates hrg is for bail to be set.  Court identifies def from previous contacts.  DA requests def to be held without bail.  Court grants as requested.  Continued initial to be set for 1/18 at 10:30 a.m.  Def remanded bact to ICJ.  Adj.  11:44 a.m.  klr
